<br>
First let me talk a little about Radiant.  I recruited with Radiant for a week about, yes only a week, and in that week we killed rumblecrush, Vindi, Sev, golems in fear, and royals in chardok in that order.  I am a firm believer in raid attendence barring RL interference so I attended all the raids I heard about to give Radiant a better chance to know me (they found out I am a little deranged!).  Radiant is a medium sized guild yet they managed to take down a mob like Vindi (yes I know it is easy for some guilds but was Radiant's first try).    We wiped the first 2 pulls of Vindi but Radiant picked itself back up and persevered enough to kill Vindi on the third try.  That is how Radiant is, yes there will be wipeouts on raids but they will always pick themselves back up, restrategize and conquer the mob that they are fighting.  We heard that Vindi was up but contrary to believing we would be unable to take down Vindi with the people we had online we maintained a sanguine attitude and said what the hell, lets give it a shot.  We are extremely confident in our own abilities to get the job done and the worse thing that can happen is the raid gets wiped a few times, you get rezzed, and go home knowing that you tried your best, and prepare for the next time you face the mob.<br>
<br>
I was extremely impressed with the mobilization and caring attitude expressed by all.  Whether letting a LC members tag along on a raid to get a shard for the VT key quest, helping a member camp the elusive shards in Sf, or helping with another guild's slaying or Ragefire, Radiant is always out and about helping each other and even non members occaisonally.  <br>
<br>
Using my sense summoned spell I Found out Sev was up, but we had only 14 people online about yet our leader Trist said that we were damn well going to try to kill him being as we had 2 warriors needing just the green scales and blade (neither was on at the time but that did not stop us) from queen. (yes, we beat the Mbers there !)  Rumples, the previous day was auctioning to buy the green scale but he woke up the next day finding it already in his possession.  A quick queen kill and he was epicced.  <br>
<br>
Radiant is a good guild and thrives on helping others.  We just got another cleric epic recently and completed another ranger epic while in hate.   We use a similar loot system as Lc where if a item drops, you send a tell to a loot officer or Trist saying you would like to put your name up for it, that is where one of the loot officers decides among a number of factors who best deserves the item.   I have yet to see one item distributed unfairly.  It is a system conducive to need...not greed.<br>
<br>
Now...back to the topic.  I was in PoH when this occured and I know from my experiences with Radiant that they would never intentionally ruin the gaming experience of others.  We were confident of our force to fight into hate instead of running to safe camp and ressing there.  We would have no cause to train it.  We pulled a few mobs to port in until it was clear to move to safecamp...there was no way we could have trained that many mobs from port in.  Trist died from sort of chain aggro that we thoought you guys had initiated.  He was summoned and promptly killed.  This may or may not have been true as there were having pulling issues all weekend in hate.  Mobs pathing strangely and such.  We make it to safecamp and mobs suddenly come out from nowhere They did not follow us to safecamp cause they did not come from that direction.  You don't get that many mobs in camp by accident.  I believe there was some insidious intent on the behalf of UP to train us.  After we killed them, we were angry and rightly so, and wanted nothing more to do with your guild though.  We ignored our impulsiveness to train you guys like you did us.  Moved on to the 2nd floor and killed stuff there where we encounted some more chain aggro (or not, as someone saw a UP member there), got a ton of mobs in camp, wiped, commenced with Cr, yada yada.  Then to top of matters you guys come up there to laugh at us?  I mean, my gosh that is just beyond immature.  It is extremely tough to get me angry but the sequence of events that occured in Hate managed it.  I did not openly say anything to UP because I prefer to avoid confrontation, not contribute to it (reason I don't usually post on the flame boards) but libelous words spoken against people who have proven to me their benevelent intent irked me like no other.    It makes me sad that events like this happen on Quellious and even more so when it involves people I have come to care about.<br>
<br>
I wasn't at the Cazel killing so not going to post my opinion on that as it would prolly be bigoted towards UP from the recent meltdown in hate.<br>
<br>
Btw, Thanks Lc for lending a hand with Rumblecrush the other day before you went to VT.  Don't know whether we needed the help or not as it was our first try on him but it was welcome nonetheless ).<br>
